_refine.details                                  
;1. HYDROGENS HAVE BEEN ADDED IN THE RIDING POSITIONS. 
2. A MET-INHIBITION PROTOCOL WAS USED FOR SELENOMETHIONINE 
INCORPORATION DURING PROTEIN EXPRESSION. THE OCCUPANCY 
OF THE SE ATOMS IN THE MSE RESIDUES WAS REDUCED TO 
0.75 TO ACCOUNT FOR THE REDUCED SCATTERING POWER DUE TO 
PARTIAL S-MET INCORPORATION 
3. ATOM RECORD CONTAINS RESIDUAL B FACTORS ONLY. 
4. RESIDUES 81-91, 312-315, 372-377 IN CHAIN A AND 
81-91, 372-377 IN CHAIN B ARE DISORDERED AND ARE NOT MODELED. 
5. LIGAND MOLECULES NAD AND TYR ARE MODELED.
;
